Ambrose Mandvulo Dlamini, Prime Minister of the Kingdom of Eswatini, virtually addressing the general debate of the 75th session of the United Nations General Assembly, on September in New York. Loey Felipe/United Nations/AFP JOHANNESBURG - The Kingdom of Eswatini has announced a state funeral for Prime Minister Ambrose Dlamini.
Dlamini was infected with COVID-19 four weeks ago and was brought to a South African hospital. READ: Eswatini Prime Minister dies after contracting COVID-19 The 52-year-old had been Prime Minister since November 2018. Before that he was the CEO of MTN Eswatini and had worked in banking for almost two decades. Eswatini has recorded nearly 7,000 COVID-19 cases and 127 deaths.